</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Inverted Row Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set up a secured barbell at a high height on a squat rack or Smith machine. It should be slightly higher than your hips so your body can hang freely.</li>



<li>Grip the bar with an overhand grip (palms down) with your hands shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Place yourself beneath the bar with your body extended, feet together, and heels on the ground. You should form a straight line from your head to your heels.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale as you squeeze your shoulder blades and pull your chest up towards the bar.</li>



<li>Hold at the top for a count, focusing on engaging your back muscles, shoulders, and biceps.</li>



<li>Inhale as you slowly lower back to the starting position, fully extending your arms.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips </h4>



<ul>
<li>Engage your core throughout the full movement to reduce strain on the lower back.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Avoid swinging or using momentum to lift yourself to maximize muscle engagement.</li>



<li>Use a bent knee position to reduce the difficulty if needed.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



